      "TradeItemDescriptionModule": {
        "TradeItemDescriptionInformation": {
          "AdditionalTradeItemDescription": [
            {
              "LanguageCode": "en",
              "Value": "The Disposable Electronic Ureteroscope（Basic UDI: 697209192ETU34KM, EMDN Code : Z12020709） is an invasive single use device and is flexible inserted portion intended for visual examination and treatment of the ureter (the upper urinary tract that connects the kidney to the bladder). It is inserted through the external urethral orifice and bladder during ureteroscopy. Anatomical images are transmitted to the user by a Image processor produced by Bonree with a CMOS chip at the distal end of the endoscope and the images showing on a monitor. This device is commonly used for biopsies, endoscopic lithotripsy, and treatment of upper urinary tract malignancies, incising strictures, and repairing ureteropelvic junction obstructions."
            }
